column5: Too bad there's no Moose season where this one was standing when I took the picture today! lol Sorry for the quality.. I was doing 70KPH with the big trailer behind with an airplane on it...
Adding salt to the wound Wayne
Ha Ha! Ya Bugger!!  We're actually contemplating going back up....some time next week or week after....just two of us...with two tags....might bring my clip this time
You in the back field tonight??
Went for a walk to see any sign....no current rubs or scrapes...prolly the next week or two for sure....

What a beautiful day today!  While cutting the runway with the tractor... I saw 20 juvenile turkeys, 2 Toms, 2 Does came bounding over the fence and across the runway and the highlight of the day...an 8 point buck that I actually had to beep the tractor horn at 5 times to get him out of my way in the centre of the runway. He must be horny if he's after the Zetor as well...
They know when and when not to show, Wayne.
Nice....  I won't be around for a week again Wayne....back up moose hunting, leaving tommorow....comin' back with a pictography and bullwinkle.  Hopefully this trip I can post a report about !
